import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data, label='Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wheat', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['wheat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of wheat production?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Wheat Production")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.barplot(x='year', y='wages', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the average wage per year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average Wages')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    correlation_matrix = data[['wheat', 'wages']].corr()
    heatmap = sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wheat production and wages?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
